Fix — apply in three layers:

LAYER 1 (immediate unblock) — Defensive default handler at every json.dump 
call across all 4 workflows.

In app.py _generate_rs_report(), _generate_ei_report()/assemble_and_generate 
(EI), _generate_deg_eg_report(), _generate_benoc_report(): change every 
json.dump call to include:

def _json_safe(o):
if isinstance(o, (set, frozenset)):
return sorted(list(o), key=str)
if hasattr(o, "isoformat"): # datetime/date
return o.isoformat()
if hasattr(o, "__dict__"):
return str(o)
return str(o)

json.dump(payload, jf, ensure_ascii=False, default=_json_safe)

This is belt-and-suspenders. Guarantees generation never fails on any 
unserializable type across any workflow.

LAYER 2 (root cause fix) — Convert at the point sets enter the payload, 
not at serialization time.

